# ============================================================================
# Audio Fix Configuration
# ============================================================================
# Set this variable when using ngrok tunnel to route Telnyx audio correctly
# 
# Why needed:
#   - Telnyx cannot reach localhost (it's on the internet)
#   - We need a public URL to expose the WebSocket endpoint
#   - ngrok creates a public tunnel to localhost:5000
#
# How to set:
#   1. Download ngrok: https://ngrok.com/download
#   2. Create free account and get auth token
#   3. Run: ngrok config add-authtoken YOUR_TOKEN
#   4. Start tunnel: ngrok http 5000
#   5. You'll see "Forwarding https://abc123.ngrok.io -> http://localhost:5000"
#   6. Set this variable to: wss://abc123.ngrok.io/openai-realtime-dialer
#   7. Also update Telnyx Call Control App with this stream_url
#
# Examples:
# PUBLIC_WEBSOCKET_URL=wss://1234-56-789.ngrok.io/openai-realtime-dialer
# PUBLIC_WEBSOCKET_URL=wss://your-subdomain.ngrok.io/openai-realtime-dialer
# PUBLIC_WEBSOCKET_URL=wss://api.yourdomain.com/openai-realtime-dialer
#
# Leave empty or commented out to use request host header (localhost development)
# ============================================================================

# Uncomment and fill with your public WebSocket URL:
# PUBLIC_WEBSOCKET_URL=wss://YOUR_NGROK_URL/openai-realtime-dialer
